(thirdQuint)Safety and Efficacy of Intramuscular Electrotransfer of Plasmid AMEP in Patients Suffering From Advanced or Metastatic Melanoma.

 In this open-label, multicentre, dose escalation phase I study, successive cohorts of 3 patients suffering from advanced or metastatic melanoma will be electrotransferred increasing doses of Plasmid AMEP into muscle.

 Treatment will be repeated every 28 days until progression or limiting toxicity.

 Consecutive cohorts of 3 to 6 patients will be treated with increasing doses of Plasmid AMEP at three dose levels: 0.

25 mg, 1 mg and 4 mg according to an adapted 3+3 design.

 There will be no intra-patient dose escalation.

